author: app.com
title: Brown's big night leads Vianney over Raritan
text:
MORE HOLMDEL – What can Brown do for you?
How about 297 yards and five touchdowns through the air, and another 108 yards on the ground?
Those were the totals for St. John Vianney quarterback Anthony Brown , as the Boston College commit led his Lancers to a 56-26 victory over Raritan on Friday, and a sixth straight win to open this 2015 season.
“Anthony had a great game, but it’s kind of like the same old thing for us,” St. John Vianney coach Derek Sinisky said. “For a lot of people who haven’t seen him play, they’ll probably see this as a great, great game by him. But to us its sort of commonplace because we’re so used to it.”
